Defendant Bradley Neal Kohlscheen in court, in custody, with attorney Walter Arthur Piel.   David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to count #1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  State makes recommendations. Attorney Behm makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  

The Court Orders the Following: Count #1.  
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of 
1 year jail without Huber.  (Credit - 94 days).  
Term of Probation: 2 Years
Conditions of Probation:
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
May not use more than one pharmacy for prescriptions;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Sign Medical Release for Agent;
Condition Time: 150 days Huber with work, work search, any court appearances, and treatment to commence forthwith.  
FINE $2340.50 to be paid as a condition of probation; failure to pay during probation, the alternate is 23 days huber.  
DNA sample previously done and not ordered.
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 to be paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to Muskego Police Department.
DL REVOCATION: Court orders 2 years revocation (will be total of 4 years administratively)
IGNITITION INTERLOCK: 2 years (while on probation)
Defendant to attend the Victim Impact Panel
Felony warnings given.
